Description: Clipped — lightweight clipboard history manager
 Monitors your clipboard and stores a history of text and images.
 Press Super+V (or your custom hotkey) to open the panel, or click
 the cat icon in the system tray.
 .
 Features:
  - Clipboard history with search and one-click paste
  - Emoji browser and Unicode symbol browser
  - Settings page with configurable hotkey
  - System tray icon (white cat)
  - Auto-starts at login
  - Works on Ubuntu 20.04 / 22.04 / 24.04, Debian, Mint and more
  - Runs via XWayland on Wayland sessions (GDK_BACKEND=x11)
